''Remarriage'' (noun or verb) implies that one or both mates has been "[[married]]" one or more times before, in someone's opinion. Remarriage involving one or both partner's existing children by prior mates forms or expands a [[stepfamily]]. [http://sfhelp.org/08/remarriage1.htm The "/" in "re/marriage"] (or re/divorce) denotes that one partner has never been married before.